race.description: Wollongong City Motors Rev & Run Provincial Handicap
race.comment: SPIRITUALISTIC (7) battled on fairly but was never a threat when first-up from a ten-week break over 1200m at Wyong last start. Will spear across from a wide gate to take up a forward position. Needs 1400m now so a much better run is anticipated. NANTUCKET ISLAND (2) won over 1200m here first-up then floundered in heavy going at Rosehill subsequently. Nicely drawn and worth another chance on top of the ground. TOKYO STAR (4) lined up for the first time in 16 months and did a great job to finish a close second over 1350m at the Beaumont track recently. Can play a role in the outcome if that effort hasn't flattened her. DRUNKEN SAILOR (5) can return to form with Costin back aboard - she gets the best out of this five-year-old.
